title: fix: ensure we do not index duplicate resource types
body:
In merge reqeust #547  @coderabbitai found there were duplicates added to the list of supported resource types.

This MR removes 5 duplicates from the current list and ensures we no longer index duplicates from the AWS documentation.

Source of the duplicates was, that AWS has actually duplicates in their list of resources: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/resource-import-supported-resources.html

#### ⚠️ Potential Breakage ⚠️

A new `impl AsRef<Uuid> for Uuid` bound has been added, which can break inference on code like:

```rust
let b = uuid.as_ref();
```

You can fix these by explicitly typing the result of the conversion:

```rust
let b: &[u8] = uuid.as_ref();
```

or by calling `as_bytes` instead:

```rust
let b = uuid.as_bytes();
```
